cs.FL, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a computational model (copyless CRA) and its expressiveness. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as the paper proposes a normal form for copyless CRA and studies the properties of a special group of registers. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper deals with a specific type of automata and its properties. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a possibility as the paper discusses the decidable subclasses of CRA. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper deals with a computational model and its properties.
